5eb3f31c-ab3a-43c0-b9b8-f1b33591c503.name: ZZ Raven
5eb3f31c-ab3a-43c0-b9b8-f1b33591c503.description: A dark version of the ZZ plant

9aafdad4-1958-4d5e-9111-ad04c4f98216.name: Syngonium Milk Confetti
9aafdad4-1958-4d5e-9111-ad04c4f98216.description: Gorgeous light-leafed syngonium with pink spots

a3aa5fb7-595d-4184-85d2-ddb561ad59d6.name: Peace lily
a3aa5fb7-595d-4184-85d2-ddb561ad59d6.description: Peace lilies are sturdy plants with glossy, dark green oval leaves that narrow to a point.

154b868a-ee11-4c83-ab5e-6023e09b2bb9.name: Sansevieria Moonshine
154b868a-ee11-4c83-ab5e-6023e09b2bb9.description: A beautiful, upright snake plant with broad silvery green leaves.

ae42bc08-2e14-48f9-a374-86edfcfe6725.name: Philodendron Pink Princess
ae42bc08-2e14-48f9-a374-86edfcfe6725.description: A climbing aroid with dark leaves and light pink variegated blotches.

2487a558-a863-48c0-8b76-6f257549d6aa.name: Curio Rowleyanus
2487a558-a863-48c0-8b76-6f257549d6aa.description: An interesting succulent grown for its unusual, bead-like leaves.

796fda40-8e0e-4b09-9c7f-ad3a5254d32e.name: Polka Dot Begonia
796fda40-8e0e-4b09-9c7f-ad3a5254d32e.description: Begonia Maculata Wightii, also known as Polka Dot Begonia, is known for its dramatic dark green leaves that look like angel’s or bat wings and silver dots.

ca954e61-33a3-4c74-b435-493b62c58bb6.name: Swiss Cheese Vine
ca954e61-33a3-4c74-b435-493b62c58bb6.description: Monstera Adansonii, also known as Swiss Cheese vine is a perfect plant for all those die hard cheese lovers that have recently developed an intolerance to lactose. This plant won’t harm your stomach.

5e7740f6-0cb4-4107-bc2e-4a5e1e673734.name: Black Velvet
5e7740f6-0cb4-4107-bc2e-4a5e1e673734.description: How does one go about selecting a piece of flora that is compatible with one’s extremely high social standing? One buys a royal plant. Introducing Queen Alocasia Reginula. She’s regal as f*ck. Buy the Queen Alocasia Reginula now!

dbb7d29b-69d4-4d25-816e-aa8bc174b6c0.name: Fiddle Leaf Fig
dbb7d29b-69d4-4d25-816e-aa8bc174b6c0.description: Ficus Lyrata, also known as fiddle leaf fig tree is a fabolous houseplant! Fiddle Leaf Fig tree gets its name from its big, fiddle-shaped leaves. It can grow to impressive sizes when given proper care.

856c8e24-e9ba-41f6-b011-e5a498104250.name: Pinstripe
856c8e24-e9ba-41f6-b011-e5a498104250.description: Calathea Ornata, also known as pinstripe has very dark almost black foliage that is lined with symmetric pink stripes. Most people when seeing this plant for the first time ask whether it is real. Ornata is one of the most ornamental house plants of the popular Calathea genus.

4aa8e5b2-3a92-4983-b00a-dc7839959fab.name: Fruit Salad
4aa8e5b2-3a92-4983-b00a-dc7839959fab.description: A true houseplant classic- the iconic Monstera Deliciosa also commonly known as fruit salad or swiss cheese plant. The split leaves are so beautiful that they’ve been extensively used in art and design.

bf68962c-7edc-45e9-9f0f-453356c87695.name: String of Hearts
bf68962c-7edc-45e9-9f0f-453356c87695.description: For all those with achy breaky hearts that seem to shatter with every new relationship, failed tinder date or slight celebrity obsession? Armour yourself with some Ceropegia Woodii for backups :)

58af33ed-a0e8-4b22-be54-ba5e2614e260.name: Fishbone Cactus
58af33ed-a0e8-4b22-be54-ba5e2614e260.description: Epiphyllum Anguliger syn Disocactus Anguliger, aka Fishbone Cactus is an epiphytic cactus with smooth, green skin and extensively branched stems native to Mexico. Epiphyllum Anguliger has deeply lobed leaves that are 3-5cm wide and up to 20cm long.

b228f302-ea6c-4d3c-9155-292c2a344801.name: Red Secret
b228f302-ea6c-4d3c-9155-292c2a344801.description: Alocasia Cuprea “Red Secret” has an extraordinary foliage that has a metallic shine to it. It is an exceptionally decorative plant! Its red-like leaves with dark almost black markings look fabulous and dramatic. This Alocasia stays compact and its suitable for terrariums.

796fda40-8e0e-4b09-9c7f-ad3a5254d32e8.name: Whale Fin
796fda40-8e0e-4b09-9c7f-ad3a5254d32e8.description: Sansevieria masoniana, also known as Whale Fin, Snake Plant or mother in law tongue is a rather slow grower however an easy to care for succulent that requires little water.

35e37387-f137-4eec-9d8d-59a6883cb0dc.name: Stingray
35e37387-f137-4eec-9d8d-59a6883cb0dc.description: ‘Stingray’ is the elephant’s ear to acquire if you’re after one-of-a-kind foliage. It gained its name with the inward curving edges and the long pointed tail that resembles the marine animal.

887b76c3-d117-4cbb-a469-5070ac028821.name: Pink Dragon
887b76c3-d117-4cbb-a469-5070ac028821.description: Alocasia Baginda Pink Dragon has green leaves with silver-like markings and bright pink stems under.  It is an exceptionally decorative plant! This Alocasia stays compact and is suitable for terrariums.

37a84a56-75a8-4dfa-934f-6804573a17a7.name: Neon Robusta
37a84a56-75a8-4dfa-934f-6804573a17a7.description: Syngonium Podophyllum ‘Neon Robusta’ has gorgeous blush pink leave coloration. It’s an easy grow plant from the Aracae family. As the plant ages it will begin to vine, therefore putting it in a hanging basket or on trellis might be a good idea!

bd9260b5-97f1-4873-a477-6c5a594bd7c9.name: Argyraeus
bd9260b5-97f1-4873-a477-6c5a594bd7c9.description: Scindapsus Pictus Argyraeu, also known as Satin Pothos, is part of the Aracae family and known for its matte green foliage with silver markings.

099dfc16-4b8f-4611-93c3-7d4ec7a0b133.name: Peacock Plant
099dfc16-4b8f-4611-93c3-7d4ec7a0b133.description: Calathea Makoyana, commonly known as the Peacock Plant is one of the most ornamental house plants of the popular Calathea genus. The Makoyana’s intricate foliage is one of the more subtle arrangements of the genus and is an essential addition to any tropical plant enthusiast. The sky reaching growth combined with a semi-transparent purple leaf underside brings both volume and aesthetics to any room.

038fc06a-398f-4436-880d-e0b77986b0fa.name: Caladium Fiesta
038fc06a-398f-4436-880d-e0b77986b0fa.description: Caladium Fiesta is a very decorative plant and a real must for all plant lovers! This Caladium white, almost transparent leaves with wide, hot pink veins.

f8555ad4-cadd-43c8-bee6-36b3ce09908b.name: Angel Wings
f8555ad4-cadd-43c8-bee6-36b3ce09908b.description: Caladium White Queen is commonly know as Angel Wings is an exceptionally decorative plant and a real must for all plant lovers! With an almost transparent white leaf, the caladium is like no other plant, a true collectors item.

18ada5ab-df2b-421a-b7d5-493f968ac494.name: Aglaonema Pink Spot
18ada5ab-df2b-421a-b7d5-493f968ac494.description: Aglaonema Pink Spot’s green leaves are stylishly spotted with pink variegation. Aglaonema is one of the easiest to grow houseplants while it’s also one of the most interesting and decorative ones.

b105575a-71f1-4d08-b33c-9442ab451cb3.name: Midnight Glory
b105575a-71f1-4d08-b33c-9442ab451cb3.description: Monolena Primuliflora ‘Midnight Glory’ is a truly eye-catching plant with bushy growth and leaves with a unique pattern that emerge bright red and slowly turn dark green as they mature.

44615c55-6476-4093-b94a-1f7126545f4e.name: Red Arrowhead
44615c55-6476-4093-b94a-1f7126545f4e.description: Homalomena ‘Red Arrowhead’ is a compact, bushy aroid with simple, yet beautiful leaves that are of a rich, velvety dark green with red undertones!

632b051b-0a7f-40b8-952d-32a25c6e98bb.name: Combat
632b051b-0a7f-40b8-952d-32a25c6e98bb.description: Coleus ‘Combat’ is a true firework of a plant! This bushy, compact plant has highly variegated, serrated leaves with irregularly splashed in orange, red, yellow and green. It is a fast-growing, easygoing perennial that will thrive as an indoor plant as well as outdoors over the summer!
